@slamd64 Is this still relevant?

FWIW `0.3.11-amd64` / `0.3.11-armd64` is some tag convention that is irrelevant to Skopeo; Skopeo does not have any concept of “related tags” like that.

The quoted command with `${FINAL_TAGS}` does not actually say what you were telling Skopeo to copy. If the command was copying `0.3.11`, I would expect the destination to contain a `0.3.11` tag with a multi-arch image (and pre-existing `0.3.11-amd64`/`0.3.11-arm64` tags, if any, to not be affected at all, and to continue to point to whatever they were pointing to previously).
